<paragraph id="574036D4FFE0416DCA81E844FD622124" blockId="22.[151,1437,223,753]" box="[199,720,295,322]" pageId="22" pageNumber="473">
Re 
<emphasis id="658BEAC6FFE0416DCAA0E84BFEE32124" bold="true" box="[230,337,295,321]" pageId="22" pageNumber="473">ferences:</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="336E4B25FFE0416DCB1EE84BFDBE2124" author="Grzeschik, K. - H." box="[344,524,295,321]" pageId="22" pageNumber="473" pagination="46 - 144" refId="ref16393" refString="Grzeschik, K. - H. (1969) On the systematics, biology and ethology of Eugaster Serville (Orthoptera, Tettigoniidae). Form and Function, 1, 46 - 144." type="journal article" year="1969">Grzeschik 1969</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="336E4B25FFE0416DC853E84BFD622124" author="Arias, A. &amp; Marquez, R. &amp; Llusia, D. &amp; Beltran, J. F. &amp; Slimani, T. &amp; Radi, M. &amp; Fattah, A. &amp; El Hassan El Mouden" box="[533,720,295,321]" pageId="22" pageNumber="473" pagination="225 - 238" refId="ref15395" refString="Arias, A., Marquez, R., Llusia, D., Beltran, J. F., Slimani, T., Radi, M., Fattah, A. &amp; El Hassan El Mouden (2012) Effects of tem- perature on the song parameters of the Moroccan bushcricket Eugaster spinulosa (Orthoptera, Tettigoniidae). Bioacoustics, 21 (3), 225 - 238. https: // doi. org / 10.1080 / 09524622.2012.686185" type="journal article" year="2012">
Arias 
<emphasis id="658BEAC6FFE0416DC81FE844FD232124" box="[601,657,295,321]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="473">et al.</emphasis>
2012
</bibRefCitation>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="574036D4FFE0416DCA81E827FCC12204" blockId="22.[151,1437,223,753]" pageId="22" pageNumber="473">
<emphasis id="658BEAC6FFE0416DCA81E827FED02100" bold="true" box="[199,354,331,357]" pageId="22" pageNumber="473">Bioacoustics.</emphasis>
All specimens of 
<taxonomicName id="90FF4D57FFE0416DC86CE820FD3D2100" authorityName="Serville" authorityYear="1838" box="[554,655,332,357]" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" genus="Eugaster" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="473" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="658BEAC6FFE0416DC86CE820FD3D2100" box="[554,655,332,357]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="473">Eugaster</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
recorded previously (
<bibRefCitation id="336E4B25FFE0416DC9C6E827FB872100" author="Grzeschik, K. - H." box="[896,1077,331,357]" pageId="22" pageNumber="473" pagination="46 - 144" refId="ref16393" refString="Grzeschik, K. - H. (1969) On the systematics, biology and ethology of Eugaster Serville (Orthoptera, Tettigoniidae). Form and Function, 1, 46 - 144." type="journal article" year="1969">Grzeschik 1969</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="336E4B25FFE0416DCE79E827FAA82100" author="Schmidt, G. H. &amp; Feierabend, H. &amp; Paiva, M. R." box="[1087,1306,331,357]" pageId="22" pageNumber="473" pagination="405 - 410" refId="ref18764" refString="Schmidt, G. H., Feierabend, H. &amp; Paiva, M. R. (1997) Ein Beitrag zum Kopulations- und Stridulationsverhalten von Eugaster guyoni fernandezii. Bolivar, 1935 (Ensifera: Hetrodidae). Mitteilungen der Deutschen Gesellschaft fur Allgemeine und Angewandte Entomologie, 11, 405 - 410." type="journal article" year="1997">
Schmidt 
<emphasis id="658BEAC6FFE0416DCEE4E820FB6B2100" box="[1186,1241,331,357]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="473">et al.</emphasis>
1997
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="336E4B25FFE0416DCF65E827FF6321EC" author="Arias, A. &amp; Marquez, R. &amp; Llusia, D. &amp; Beltran, J. F. &amp; Slimani, T. &amp; Radi, M. &amp; Fattah, A. &amp; El Hassan El Mouden" pageId="22" pageNumber="473" pagination="225 - 238" refId="ref15395" refString="Arias, A., Marquez, R., Llusia, D., Beltran, J. F., Slimani, T., Radi, M., Fattah, A. &amp; El Hassan El Mouden (2012) Effects of tem- perature on the song parameters of the Moroccan bushcricket Eugaster spinulosa (Orthoptera, Tettigoniidae). Bioacoustics, 21 (3), 225 - 238. https: // doi. org / 10.1080 / 09524622.2012.686185" type="journal article" year="2012">
Arias 
<emphasis id="658BEAC6FFE0416DCF23E820FA2F2100" box="[1381,1437,331,357]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="473">et al.</emphasis>
2012
</bibRefCitation>
) and by us, showed a calling song consisting of a series of short echemes (
<figureCitation id="CFC42A51FFE0416DCE48E803FBD721EF" box="[1038,1125,367,394]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="8.[151,250,1254,1278]" captionTargetBox="[158,1423,198,1221]" captionTargetId="figure-23@8.[151,1436,181,1231]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 5. Oscillograms of song types in Hetrodini. Song consisting A of long trills (Cosmoderus femoralis CH8627), B of broken trills (including transitions to long echemes; B1 Spalacomimus talpa, B2 Enyaliopsis jennae, B3 Enyaliopsis ephippiatus) or C of regularly repeated echemes (C1 Spalacomimus spec. near verruciferus, C2 Eugaster guyoni). 1-min-sections." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6392721" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6392721/files/figure.png" pageId="22" pageNumber="473">Fig. 5C</figureCitation>
<figureCitation id="CFC42A51FFE0416DCE22E803FBC121EF" box="[1124,1139,367,394]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1837,1861]" captionTargetBox="[166,1420,1232,1814]" captionTargetId="figure-207@4.[151,1436,1216,1814]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 2. Left and right male tegmina of A Cosmoderus femoralis (CH8627), B Enyaliopsis bloyeti (CH8853), C Eugaster guyoni (CH0656), D Spalacomimus spec. near verruciferus (CH7898). Scale 5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6392713" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6392713/files/figure.png" pageId="22" pageNumber="473">2</figureCitation>
; 
<figureCitation id="CFC42A51FFE0416DCE39E803FAB621EF" box="[1151,1284,367,394]" captionStart="FIGURE 10" captionStartId="14.[151,250,1322,1346]" captionTargetBox="[156,1433,260,1291]" captionTargetId="figure-48@14.[151,1436,237,1299]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURE 10. Oscillograms of the calling songs in the genera Eugaster, Eugasteroides and Spalacomimus (figures of S. liberianus based on figures and data from literature; see text). A Eugaster guyoni, B Eugaster spinulosa, C Eugasteroides loricatus, D Spalacomimus liberianus, E Spalacomimus magnus, F Spalacomimus stettinensis, G Spalacomimus talpa, H Spalacomimus verruciferus, I Spalacomimus spec. near verruciferus." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6392739" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6392739/files/figure.png" pageId="22" pageNumber="473">Fig. 10A, B</figureCitation>
; see 
<tableCitation id="1A7D036FFFE0416DCF7CE803FA3D21EC" box="[1338,1423,367,393]" captionStart="TABLE 2" captionStartId="7.[151,236,476,501]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="TABLE 2. Song characteristics of Hetrodini species (for song type see Fig. 5 and text)" httpUri="http://table.plazi.org/id/0380665CFFF1417CCAD1E8B0FBBD2190" pageId="22" pageNumber="473" tableUuid="0380665CFFF1417CCAD1E8B0FBBD2190">Table 2</tableCitation>
). Each echeme contains between 8 and 12 (once 14; see 
<bibRefCitation id="336E4B25FFE0416DC8B5E8FFFC1621CB" author="Grzeschik, K. - H." box="[755,932,403,430]" pageId="22" pageNumber="473" pagination="46 - 144" refId="ref16393" refString="Grzeschik, K. - H. (1969) On the systematics, biology and ethology of Eugaster Serville (Orthoptera, Tettigoniidae). Form and Function, 1, 46 - 144." type="journal article" year="1969">Grzeschik 1969</bibRefCitation>
) syllables. The SRR in these recording varies between 21 and 53 Hz at different and often unknown temperatures. For 
<collectionCode id="31EEAE11FFE0416DC989E8D4FBB721B7" box="[975,1029,440,466]" pageId="22" pageNumber="473">ERR</collectionCode>
fewer data are available (1–3.4 Hz) but here a strong and quite strict relationship with temperature is documented with a factor of about four between 15 and 35ºC (
<bibRefCitation id="336E4B25FFE0416DCB69E893FE7B227C" author="Nielsen, E. T." box="[303,457,511,537]" pageId="22" pageNumber="473" pagination="325 - 347" refId="ref18344" refString="Nielsen, E. T. (1974) Activity patterns of Eugaster (Orthoptera: Ensifera). Entomologia Experimentalis et Applicata, 17, 325 - 347. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / j. 1570 - 7458.1974. tb 00351. x" type="journal article" year="1974">Nielsen 1974</bibRefCitation>
). So at present in our opinion there are no data that prove song differences between any named forms. The number of teeth in the stridulatory files is also quite similar between subspecies/species, ranging from 41.4 to 48.0 (means with n =5–30; 
<bibRefCitation id="336E4B25FFE0416DC818EB2BFCA32204" author="Grzeschik, K. - H." box="[606,785,583,609]" pageId="22" pageNumber="473" pagination="46 - 144" refId="ref16393" refString="Grzeschik, K. - H. (1969) On the systematics, biology and ethology of Eugaster Serville (Orthoptera, Tettigoniidae). Form and Function, 1, 46 - 144." type="journal article" year="1969">Grzeschik 1969</bibRefCitation>
, p. 103).
</paragraph>
